title: The Lost Weekend
overview: The desperate life of a chronic alcoholic is followed through a four-day drinking bout.

title: Ace in the Hole
overview: A frustrated former big-city journalist now stuck working for an Albuquerque newspaper exploits a story about a man trapped in a cave to rekindle his career, but the situation quickly escalates into an out-of-control circus.

title: Sweet Smell of Success
overview: Powerful but unethical Broadway columnist J.J. Hunsecker coerces unscrupulous press agent Sidney Falco into breaking up his sister's romance with a jazz musician.

title: Gilda
overview: A small-time gambler hired to work in a Buenos Aires casino discovers his employer's new wife is his former lover.

title: Laura
overview: A police detective falls in love with the woman whose murder he is investigating.

title: In a Lonely Place
overview: A potentially violent screenwriter is a murder suspect until his lovely neighbor clears him. However, she soon starts to have her doubts.

title: Kai po che!
overview: Three friends growing up in India at the turn of the millennium set out to open a training academy to produce the country's next cricket stars.

title: Jodaeiye Nader az Simin
overview: A married couple are faced with a difficult decision - to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer's disease.

title: Belle de jour
overview: A frigid young housewife decides to spend her midweek afternoons as a prostitute.

title: Sling Blade
overview: Karl Childers, a simple man hospitalized since his childhood murder of his mother and her lover, is released to start a new life in a small town.

title: Midnight Cowboy
overview: A naive hustler travels from Texas to New York City to seek personal fortune, finding a new friend in the process.

title: Boogie Nights
overview: Back when sex was safe, pleasure was a business and business was booming, an idealistic porn producer aspires to elevate his craft to an art when he discovers a hot young talent.

title: Kis Uykusu
overview: A hotel owner and landlord in a remote Turkish village deals with conflicts within his family and a tenant behind on his rent.

title: Million Dollar Baby
overview: A determined woman works with a hardened boxing trainer to become a professional.

title: Hiroshima mon amour
overview: A French actress filming an anti-war film in Hiroshima has an affair with a married Japanese architect as they share their differing perspectives on war.

title: Il conformista
overview: A weak-willed Italian man becomes a fascist flunky who goes abroad to arrange the assassination of his old teacher, now a political dissident.

title: Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?
overview: A bitter, aging couple, with the help of alcohol, use their young houseguests to fuel anguish and emotional pain towards each other over the course of a distressing night.

title: American History X
overview: A former neo-nazi skinhead tries to prevent his younger brother from going down the same wrong path that he did.

title: Network
overview: A television network cynically exploits a deranged former anchor's ravings and revelations about the news media for its own profit.

title: Portrait de la jeune fille en feu
overview: On an isolated island in Brittany at the end of the eighteenth century, a female painter is obliged to paint a wedding portrait of a young woman.
